post_cb({"13816778": {"ViewCount": "304", "Body": "<p>By C++11 standard <code>std::is_base_of&lt;B, D&gt;</code> must return true if D is derived from B or if both are the same non-union class. But in VC++ 2010 stl implementation template return true if the type B is a ONLY base class of the type D! Is it a bug ?</p>\n<p>At <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb982243(v=vs.100).aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb982243(v=vs.100).aspx</a> page in example section </p>\n<pre><code>std::is_base_of&lt;base, base&gt; == true\n</code></pre>\n<p>but this does not correspond VC++2010 STL implementation. Although it is consistent with the requirement of the C++11 standard. Where is a bug ?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "13817530", "Title": "VC2010 implementation of std::is_base_of contains a bug?", "CreationDate": "2012-12-11T08:59:40.887", "Id": "13816778", "CommentCount": "3", "FavoriteCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2012-12-11T22:13:10.197", "LastEditorUserId": "636019", "LastActivityDate": "2012-12-11T22:13:10.197", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "987850", "Tags": "<c++><visual-studio-2010><visual-c++><c++11><std>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_13816778_13817530_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 4716}}, "n3337": {"so_13816778_13817530_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 4523}}, "n4659": {"so_13816778_13817530_0": {"length": 15, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 6114}}}, "13817530": {"Id": "13817530", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p><code>is_base_of&lt;int, int&gt;::value</code> evaluates to <code>false</code> (your comment indicates that this is the actual question you have) because <code>is_base_of&lt;&gt;::value</code> can evaluate to <code>true</code> only if the template parameters are class types. The C++11 standard's Table 51 - Type relationship predicates (C++ 20.9.6 \"Relationships between types\") defines <code>is_base_type&lt;&gt;</code> to evaluate to true if and only if (emphasis added):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_13816778_13817530_0\">Base is a base class of Derived without regard to cv-qualifiers or Base and Derived are not unions and name the same <strong>class type</strong> without regard to cv-qualifiers</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The C++11 standard even has the following as one of its examples (C++11 20.9.6/3):</p>\n<blockquote id=\"so_13816778_13817530_1\">\n<pre><code>is_base_of&lt;int, int&gt;::value // false\n</code></pre>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "12711", "LastActivityDate": "2012-12-11T09:53:25.910", "Score": "7", "CreationDate": "2012-12-11T09:47:45.670", "ParentId": "13816778", "CommentCount": "2", "OwnerUserId": "12711", "LastEditDate": "2012-12-11T09:53:25.910"}});